{title: It Should Have Been Easy}
{artist: Anne Murray}
{composer: Written by Bob McDill}

[G]Every morning when I get up
I see your face in my coffee cup
Looking [C]back at me looking [G]back at me
Another morning another day
And still I’m feeling the same old way
I’m still [C]missing you missing [G]you
[C]It should have been [G]easy
It [D7]should have been [G]easy
[C]It should have been [G]oh so easy to [C]do
But I’m still getting [D7]over [G]you
I keep seeing old friends of mine
They all smile and they say in time
I’ll get [C]over you I’ll be [G]good as new
I guess somehow some day I will
I’ll forget you I know but still
It’ll [C]take some time it’ll take some [G]time
Repeat #2 x2
